snippet: The government-controlled mortgage company is seeking $800 million in damages
abstract: Government-controlled mortgage company Fannie Mae sues nine of the world's largest banks, accusing them of colluding to suppress the Libor interest rate, and seeking more than $800 million of damages.
lead_paragraph: The government-controlled mortgage company is seeking $800 million in damages

headline.main: Fannie Mae Sues 9 Banks Over Libor
